&lt;The Kindred&gt;<br>
Gawaine<br>
50 Crush Merc<br>
<br>
Kriege<br>
44 Tri-Spec Cleric</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tatsumaruiii>TatsumaruIII</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.theotaku.com/trigun/pictures/trigun12/Simage_12.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 147<br> <font color=#000000>(6/21/03 2:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=263.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.theotaku.com/trigun/pictures/trigun12/Simage_12.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Specific Feedback: Flank/DS/DT Changes</span><hr size=1> Flank - I'm impressed with the increased damage. It's hard as all living heck to land still with no to-hit, and I must spam it 3-4 times befor it lands. Shadows rain, the follow up, has a to-hit so thankfully that one often lands. If we ever got our DW to do advanced spec damage, this style might actually be doing too much damage. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :eek --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/eek.gif ALT=":eek"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   But for now, the damage is there. All it needs is a to-hit and it has an even more welcomed spot on my q-bar.<br>
<br>
Duel Shadows - Nice. The defense penalty isn't terrably big, but it does make a difference, so it really should go. The bleed is good for fluff. I don't see it winning any battles for me, but 25-ish extra damage on targets with little to no resists is.. ok. The damage it can do isn't all that much better than amy slash (problem I feel is shared with most/all of our styles), but it's enough to make me use it when I remember to. Just needs to hit for more damage, and i'll even replace it with my amy-slash. Over-all, moderate change. Good for a tad bit more damage, so I can't say it's a bad change. Still needs work, but that's one foot out of the grave.<br>
<br>
Dark Tendrils - Won't call this a fix. They just moved it so it's now a style we can use much more frequently. It still lacks desire to use compared to reflection/hypno, damage and effect wise. I am displeased that we no longer have anything off evade (Even though the style sucks, and we only evade every leap year, it was still nice to use it when I did evade. Gave me a sense of a full-fledge positional fighter. I would really like something cool to use after we evade, even if we don't get evade 2).<br>
<br>
All in All, with the merc changes.. I'm moderatly pleased with the changes. We got something, that's good. Flank and Duel Shadows changes, I felt, were not our main problems and the time would have been better spent on fixing other things. DT was the only main fix in there, the other two I considered to be side-fixes. I'm glad we got looked at though. About time they stopped ignoring us.<br>
<br>
I am deeply scared that we will be ingored for another year+. We still NEED more stuff done to be a challenge out in real RvR. We are still considered pests and not a real threat right now, but a bit more pesterish than befor. If this is all we get for now, and won't get anymore changes for along time.. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p>&quot;We will never be what Mythic promised we would when DAoC started, we might as well adapt or delete.&quot; -Avandor<br>
Lothire - 50 Mercenary<br>
Voas - 24 Scout</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=k8tpitta>k8tpitta</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0> at: 6/21/03 10:12 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=k8tpitta>k8tpitta</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mercenary TL</span><br>  Posts: 421<br> <font color=#000000>(6/21/03 10:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=263.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.blargle.com/boardstuff/fuu3.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Specific Feedback: Flank/DS/DT Changes</span><hr size=1> Dark Tendrils had the bleed increased. I actually requested that the evade component be removed due to the fact taht we don't evade. You can still use Twin Return/Orbit chain if you want an evade reactionary.<br>
