<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>N.A.L.F.E.N</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:black;font-family:helvetica;font-size:x-small;">Newly Appointed Leader For Emain Nutsies</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nalfen>Nalfen</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://mapage.noos.fr/philemon.levesque/nalfen.gif" BORDER=0> at: 6/22/03 11:02 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kiamarvigilance>Kiamar Vigilance</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#000000>(6/22/03 7:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=263.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Specific Feedback: Flank/DS/DT Changes</span><hr size=1> The increased bleed damage with Dual shadows is a nice improvement that was needed to compete against the Amethyst/Diamond slash combo for use on the hotbar.<br>
<br>
There is no point using Flank/DT combo at any time including if you are perpetually fighting people on their side in every single engagement. The no-hit bonus is the biggest reason besides the difficulty in actually positioning yourself properly. The benefit is hardly noticeable. This combo isn't nearly as effective as the rear positional combo in the LA line or the side postional stun combo in the CD line or the side postional stun in the Savage HTH line. It boils down to the fact that the damage output from this combo, even improved, is still only comparable to other combos that are much easier to execute. I suggest either adding in a smal duration stun component or some kind of damage proc to this combo along with atleast a small to-hit bonus on the opener.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=uhno>uhno</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.grumbled.com/images/paradoxicon.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 53<br> <font color=#000000>(6/23/03 4:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=263.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Specific Feedback: Flank/DS/DT Changes</span><hr size=1> Dual shadows bleed is nice. In RvR it's a great way to start a fight and if someone is silly enough to stand in front of you and let you spam DS it really will work wonders.<br>
Against single mobs it is almost like having a damage add.<br>
<br>
The rest of the &quot; fixes&quot; aren't even bandaids. Flank won't be used too often by me and dark tendrils won't either. If a mobs stunned or mezzed I'd still rather get off a dual shadows and the higher bleed.<br>
<br>
Can we have a great rear positional. I still like backslash better then the dual wield chain.<br>
<br>
Thanks, <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.paradoxguild.com/images/uhnosig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
<!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Level 50 Cleric/Level 50 Minstrel/Level 50 Mercenary</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END-->   <!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>GM     of     Paradox</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> </div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fester@lighttanksofdaoc>Fester</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#000000>(6/23/03 5:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=263.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Specific Feedback: Flank/DS/DT Changes</span><hr size=1> Flank/SR - The no-hit bonus is awful. This style never lands. I have lined up Flank on Mezzed/Stunned people and still missed. I try to use this style but it really is quite bad, even with the side arc degree change. Mobs also still twist when stunned. I have done the Reflect/HD combo and moved to the side and have had flank miss twice when the mob turned towards me (Shredders). Most of the time I just say the hell with it and just do Dual Shadows. The bleed compenstates for the slight damage bonus that Flank/SR gets. <br>
<br>
Dual Shadows - this style works really well now.The bleed is good. The damage is so-so (kind of low for a level 50 style) and luckily most people fight you from the front in RvR.  The defense modifier has to go. This is not like the LW Anhillation style where you get a 9 second stun.  We can't run around and stun a whole enemy group like Champs and Heros can. We don't get a large proc like Reavers get on Leviathian. No need for defense decrease at all.  There should be no debate that Dual Shadows should be greater than Amyth + Diamond but its not. <br>
<br>
Dark Tendrils - this style is ok to have your bar for PvE fighting only. In RvR you will always use the Relflection/HD combo with a backup of Dual Shadows or Amyth. The battles go so fast that 1 stun is all your need before you take down a person. In mob fighting, you can do a Ref/HD and still have tons of parries afterwards which you can us Tendrils on.  This style doesn't stay on my hot bar at all.<br>
<br>
Shadows Edge/Penumbra - not a good combo. Better off using Blackslash twice as it has better damage and a higher chance to hit both times.<br>
<br>
